<subSubSection id="C3216524FFDCFFA1FF43FA8FFBA3F814" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8436AFFFDCFFA1FF43FA8FFB89F919" blockId="5.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FF43FA8FFEA1FAC9" author="Saint-Hilaire, A." box="[136,362,1310,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="289 - 295" refId="ref8353" refString="Saint-Hilaire, A. (1828) LXVI Luhea Willd. Flora Brasiliae meridionalis 1 (8): 289 - 295." type="journal article" year="1828">Saint-Hilaire (1828)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention any specimen in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FC6CFA8EFBD5FAC9" authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1828" box="[935,1054,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FC6CFA8EFBD5FAC9" box="[935,1054,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but three of his original specimens with the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FEE6FAD2FE6EFAAD" authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1828" box="[301,421,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FEE6FAD2FE6EFAAD" box="[301,421,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are in P and in MPU herbaria, where his collections are kept (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FB90FAD3FA94FAAD" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[1115,1375,1346,1372]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 1064). The specimens found in P present the data that contradict those cited in the protologue. In P00604308, an original label by Saint-Hilaire is found with the inscription “ 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FC83FA1BFBC4FA55" box="[840,1039,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FC83FA1BFC39FA55" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[840,1010,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luhea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">Luhea uniflora</taxonomicName>
+
</emphasis>
” without the locality, together with another label with Claussen’s calligraphy and the erroneous travel period of Saint-Hilaire (1816–1821 instead of 1816–1822). In P00604307, an original label by Saint-Hilaire is found with “ 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FC2EFA43FB70FA1D" box="[997,1211,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">
1 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FC31FA43FB6AFA1D" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[1018,1185,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luhea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">Luhea uniflora</taxonomicName>
+
</emphasis>
”, but with a sentence added later by another author (different spelling) and with the erroneous travel period as above. Based on this evidence, we do not consider the locality (Minas Gerais) reported on to these specimens as reliable and attribute them instead to the same collection as that reported in the protologue (Rio de Janeiro), as duplicates of the original material. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FAA9F9AFFF18F98C" author="Cunha, M. C. S." pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFDCFFA1FAA9F9AFFA60F9A9" box="[1378,1451,1598,1624]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated the specimen in P as the ‘holotype’, without having seen it and specifying its identification number. However, this designation should be corrected as a first-step typification (Art. 9.17 of the ICN). In accordance with Arts. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN, we designated herein specimen P00604308 as the second-step 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFDCFFA1FB4DF93BFB26F935" box="[1158,1261,1706,1732]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FADAF93AFA42F935" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[1297,1417,1706,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luhea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FADAF93AFA42F935" box="[1297,1417,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by choosing the most representative specimen according to the protologue’s description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8436AFFFDCFFA1FF76F963FBA3F814" blockId="5.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FF76F963FE1CF8FD" author="Saint-Hilaire, A." box="[189,471,1778,1804]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="289 - 295" refId="ref8353" refString="Saint-Hilaire, A. (1828) LXVI Luhea Willd. Flora Brasiliae meridionalis 1 (8): 289 - 295." type="journal article" year="1828">Saint-Hilaire (1828: 291)</bibRefCitation>
reports that 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FDAAF962FD13F8FD" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[609,728,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luhea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FDAAF962FD13F8FD" box="[609,728,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FCC6F962FC57F8FD" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1826" box="[781,924,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candicans">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FCC6F962FC57F8FD" box="[781,924,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. candicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are related, but the short description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FA9FF963FEC0F8C1" author="Martius, C. F. P. V." pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="98 - 102" refId="ref7849" refString="Martius, C. F. P. V. (1826) XXXII Luhea Willd. Nova genera et species plantarum: quas in itinere per Brasiliam MDCCCXVII-MDCCCXX 1 (4): 98 - 102." type="journal article" year="1826">Martius (1826: 102)</bibRefCitation>
does not allow for any certainty. After analyzing both the Martius material for 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FBB0F886FAC1F8C1" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1826" box="[1147,1290,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candicans">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FBB0F886FAC1F8C1" box="[1147,1290,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. candicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the Saint-Hilaire material for 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FEA1F8AAFD3FF8A4" authority=", Schumann (1886: 154)" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityPageNumber="154" authorityYear="1886" box="[362,756,1850,1877]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luhea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FEA1F8AAFE28F8A5" box="[362,483,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. uniflora</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FE39F8ABFD3FF8A4" author="Schumann, K." box="[498,756,1850,1877]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886: 154)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
concluded that both belong to the same species. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FA5EF8AAFF29F889" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luhea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FA5EF8AAFF29F889" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was wrongly chosen by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FE37F8CFFD0EF888" author="Schumann, K." box="[508,709,1886,1913]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
as the putatively correct name, as he himself reported as follows: “… 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FF7BF812FA53F86D" box="[176,1432,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">itaque nomen ab St-Hilaire speciei impositum praetuli, neque vereor ne contra leges prioritatis peccaverim</emphasis>
”. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FEE5F836FDCCF830" author="Burret, K. E. M." box="[302,519,1958,1985]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="592 - 880" refId="ref7098" refString="Burret, K. E. M. (1926) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Tiliaceen. Notizblatt des Botanischen Gartens und Museums zu Berlin-Dahlem 9 (88): 592 - 880. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3994327" type="journal article" year="1926">Burret (1926: 826)</bibRefCitation>
, in the light of Schumann’s analysis, recognized the priority of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FB23F836FAB1F831" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1826" box="[1256,1402,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candicans">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FB23F836FAB1F831" box="[1256,1402,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. candicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDCFFA1FEC3F85AFE4BF815" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[264,384,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luhea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDCFFA1FEC3F85AFE4BF815" box="[264,384,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">L. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym, as also confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDCFFA1FCD6F85BFC73F814" author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[797,952,1994,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="185" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFDCFFA1FCD6F85BFCADF815" box="[797,870,1994,2020]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="5" pageNumber="185">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
and this report.
</paragraph>
